<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,1633,1899]" box="[264,366,1633,1658]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis box="[264,366,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,1633,1899]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The 
<typeStatus box="[367,469,1673,1699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
is in poor condition (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Malloch" box="[837,1016,1673,1699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="21" refString="Malloch, J. R. (1934) Muscidae. In: Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile, 7 (2), 171 - 346." type="journal article" year="1934">
Malloch, 
<number box="[952,1016,1673,1699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1934.0">1934</number>
</bibRefCitation>
): head, right fore leg, left mid leg and left hind leg missing; the other legs glued to the staging mount; abdomen loosely attached to thorax. The 
<typeStatus box="[655,758,1753,1779]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
is labelled with an old handwritten label “Pt. Fam.”; a printed label “Port Famine, / T. del Fuego. / C. Darwin.”; a further label “ 
<number box="[275,335,1833,1859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1863.0">1863</number>
– 
<number box="[351,383,1833,1859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="44.0">44</number>
. [handwritten] / Darwin Coll. [printed]”; it is also labelled as 
<typeStatus box="[1114,1172,1833,1859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Type</typeStatus>
by Malloch, and with the combination in 
<taxonomicName box="[600,795,1873,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brachygasterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[600,795,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Brachygasterina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Carvalho.
</paragraph>
